definition.value: Pterin acetylated on N-2 and carrying a formyl group at position 6.
A  hydroxy-1,4-naphthoquinone that is 1,4-naphthoquinone in which the hydrogens at positions 2 and 5 are substituted by methyl and hydroxy groups, respectively.
A hexadecenoate that is the conjugate base of (7Z)-hexadecenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A dotriacontapentaenoate that is the conjugate base of (14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-dotriacontapentaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acylsphinganine-1-phosphoethanolamine in which the N-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl.
A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid component is specified as sphinganine.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 6-methoxycarbonylhexanoyl.
A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid component is specified as phytosphingosine.
An N-acylphytosphingosine-1-phosphoethanolamine in which the N-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl.
A hydrochloride salt prepared from anileridine and two molar equivalents of hydrogen chloride.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (5Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoic acid.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (8Z,11Z)-icosadienoic acid.
A zwitterionic group obtained by transfer of a proton from the amino to the phosphate group of 5-methylaminomethyl-2-selenouridine 5'-monophosphate residue.
Any aldoxime derived from an aliphatic aldehyde.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (9Z,12Z)-tetradecadienoic acid.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (9Z,12Z)-pentadecadienoic acid.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (9Z,12Z)-heptadecadienoic acid.
An organic anionic group that is the conjugate base of CMP residue, obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.
An octadecadienoic acid in which the two double bonds have Z-geochemistry and are located at positions 6 and 9.
A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of the hydroxy group in cholesterol with the carboxy group of stearic acid.
A cholesterol ester obtained by the formal condensation of the hydroxy group in cholesterol with the carboxy group of arachidonic acid.

A carboxamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of octanoic acid with the primary amino group of (1R,2R)-2-amino-1-(2,3-dihydro-1,4-benzodioxin-6-yl)-3-(pyrrolidin-1-yl)propan-1-ol. A ceramide glucosyltransferase inhibitor used (as its tartrate salt) for treatment of Gaucher's disease.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol in which the acyl group is specified as oleoyl.
A member of the family of microcins comprising a heptapeptide covalently liinked to 3-aminopropyl-AMP via an acylphosphoramide linkage. A potent inhibitor of aspartyl-tRNA synthetase.
An organic heterotetracyclic compound and 19-membered macrocyclic lactam that is maytansine in which one of the hydrogens of the terminal N-acetyl group is replaced by a sulfanylmethyl group.
An EC 6.1.1.* (ligases forming aminoacyl tRNA and related compounds) inhibitor that specifically inhibits the action of aspartate--tRNA ligase (EC 6.1.1.12).
A member of the class of naphthoates that is 1-naphthoate substituted at positions 2 and 5 by hydroxy and methyl groups respectively; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of tripyrroles that is a red-coloured pigment with antibiotic properties produced by Serratia marcescens.
A ketoaldehyde that is octanal carrying an acetyl substituent at position 3 (the S-enantiomer).

Any member of the group of 19-membered lactams that is maytansine or structurally related to it. Maytansinoids have been isolated from members of the higher plant families Celastraceae, Rhamnaceae, and Euphorbiaceae, as well as some mosses and certain Actinomycetes, but the term is used to cover both naturally occurring compounds and their semisynthetic derivatives.
A family of cysteine-rich polypeptides that function as host defence peptides and consist of 18-45 amino acids including six to eight cysteine residues.
1-acyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol in which the 1-acyl group is specified as oleoyl.
A 1-acyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1-acyl substituent is specified as heptadecanoyl
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as S-2-methylbutanoyl.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-diphosphate(3-) arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycerol 3-diphosphate.
A glucosylglycerol consisting of an alpha-D-glucosyl residue attached at position 2 of glycerol via a glycosidic bond.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 4-(5-O-phospho-beta-D-ribofuranosyl)phenol; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the five amino groups of caldopentamine.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of four of the five amino groups of caldopentamine.
An abietane diterpenoid lacking the isopropyl substituent with an aromatic C-ring and a hydroxy group at the 12-position.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the four amino groups of N(4)-aminopropylspermidine.
A quaternary ammonium ion obtained by protonation of the four primary amino groups of N(4)-bis(aminopropyl)spermidine.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the five amino groups of N(4)-aminopropylspermine.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of (R)-3-phosphomevalonic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of (R)-3,5-bisphosphomevalonic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A 5'-deoxyribonucleoside in which hypoxanthine is attached to 5-deoxyribofuranose via a beta-N(9)-glycosidic bond.
Any silver nanoparticle that is specially coated to produce tailored nanoparticles for specific applications.
